Title#1: Raging Grannies of Denver Protest Events pt. 1
Abstract#1: A series of clips that showcase the Raging of Grannies of Denver performing at a variety of events around Colorado. The clips include parody songs that highlight United States power inequalities, anti-Iraq war, and environmentalist sentiments.

Abstract#1: A recording of KGNU's pre-recorded event at the Avenue Theater hosted by Bob Wells and Dave Johnson. The recording includes political satire news and interview sections interspersed with the Raging Grannies of Denver performing parody songs and talking about their activist work. Topics in the radio show program include the Iraq War, politics, Barak Obama, Hilary Clinton, immigration, Joe Biden, Carrie McCandless scandal, and Molly Ivins.
Note#1: 00:00:00 The recording begins with Bob Wells and Dave Johnson introducing on KGNU the Avenue Theater's pre-recorded concert of the Raging Grannies of Denver. They discuss upcoming programming and events at the Avenue Theater. 00:05:59 Wells and Johnson introduce the news comedy segment. 00:35:34 Wells and Johnson introduce the Raging Grannies for their performance. The Raging Grannies begin their performance. 00:40:09 The Raging Grannies introduce themselves. 00:40:32 Wells and Johnson ask the Raging Grannies questions about when and how they started, how they write their songs, where they get invited to sing, and what causes they support. 00:46:18 Raging Grannies discuss how to book them for future events. 00:46:56 The Raging Grannies perform more songs. 00:50:58 Wells and Johnson introduce a new comedy segment on criminal stupidity. 00:57:37 The Raging Grannies perform another song. 00:58:47 Wells and Johnson end the show and broadcast. 01:00:25 End of recording.
